      "message": "Agreed. I kept this as-is since it\u0027s the only function that uses computeFastStrokeBounds() instead of computeFastBounds(), so it already didn\u0027t quite fit the mold of the new quick_reject helper. I think computing the bounds/knowing the bounds is always worth it if there\u0027s an image filter, but do agree that letting the user provide the bounds is better. Perhaps we can just add a drawPoints() that takes an SkVertices object?",
