      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T15:52:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It took me a moment to work through it, so I\u0027ve added some comments explaining it. I also added a regular quickReject() call that uses the vertices\u0027 bounds. We can\u0027t use quick_reject helper or pass bounds to AutoLayerForImageFilter (inside DRAW_BEGIN), because they both call computeFastBounds() based on the paint.\n\ndrawVertices (and drawPatch()) completely ignore all the geometric styling of the paint that could modify the overall bounds incorrectly. It may be worthwhile, in a later change, to have SkCanvas canonize incoming SkPaints for all these draw functions, similar to how it handles paints for the drawImage family.",
